"v.移动一点儿；改变立场 【英】 v.移动一点(to move a little)；妥协(to yield) 【考】 obdurate(diehard): budge / lachrymose : cheer(顽固的不会让步/悲 哀的不会高兴) 【记】 比较：budget(预算) ，去掉一个't'就成了 'budge' 【例】 I bargained hard,but the shop owner did not budge a bit. v. 微微移动一点 = move a little; 妥协(改变立场或态度) = yield 【例】He can'apos;t budge this rock 他搬不动这块岩石. Money can'apos;t budge her 金钱不能使她改变立场. 【记】budget(n 预算), 去掉t(微微移动一点)就变成了‘budge’ 【类】obdurate[diehard]: budge = lachrymose: cheer = hidebound: innovation顽固的[人]不会让步 = 悲哀的不会高兴 = 死板的不会创新palter: candor = vagary: predict 含糊其词不会直率 = 奇特行为不会预知 【记】音：甭挤，不挤，不要挤，往里挪一挪，动一动了，挤公共汽车时常听到售票员这么说 budge (v.)  1580s, from Middle French bougier ""to move, stir"" (Modern French bouger), from Vulgar Latin *bullicare ""to bubble, boil"" (hence, ""to be in motion""), from Latin bullire ""to boil"" (see boil (v.)). Compare Spanish bullir ""to move about, bustle;"" Portuguese bulir ""to move a thing from its place."" Related: Budged; budging."
